  "root_text": {
    "an5.36:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5.36 ",
    "an5.36:0.2": "4. Sumanavagga ",
    "an5.36:0.3": "Kāladānasutta ",
    "an5.36:1.1": "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, kāladānāni. ",
    "an5.36:1.2": "Katamāni pañca? ",
    "an5.36:1.3": "Āgantukassa dānaṁ deti; ",
    "an5.36:1.4": "gamikassa dānaṁ deti; ",
    "an5.36:1.5": "gilānassa dānaṁ deti; ",
    "an5.36:1.6": "dubbhikkhe dānaṁ deti; ",
    "an5.36:1.7": "yāni tāni navasassāni navaphalāni tāni paṭhamaṁ sīlavantesu patiṭṭhāpeti. ",
    "an5.36:1.8": "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, pañca kāladānānīti. ",
    "an5.36:2.1": "Kāle dadanti sappaññā, ",
    "an5.36:2.2": "vadaññū vītamaccharā; ",
    "an5.36:2.3": "Kālena dinnaṁ ariyesu, ",
    "an5.36:2.4": "ujubhūtesu tādisu. ",
    "an5.36:3.1": "Vippasannamanā tassa, ",
    "an5.36:3.2": "vipulā hoti dakkhiṇā; ",
    "an5.36:3.3": "Ye tattha anumodanti, ",
    "an5.36:3.4": "veyyāvaccaṁ karonti vā; ",
    "an5.36:3.5": "Na tena dakkhiṇā ūnā, ",
    "an5.36:3.6": "tepi puññassa bhāgino. ",
    "an5.36:4.1": "Tasmā dade appaṭivānacitto, ",
    "an5.36:4.2": "Yattha dinnaṁ mahapphalaṁ; ",
    "an5.36:4.3": "Puññāni paralokasmiṁ, ",
    "an5.36:4.4": "Patiṭṭhā honti pāṇinan”ti. ",
    "an5.36:4.5": "Chaṭṭhaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an5.36:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 5.36 ",
    "an5.36:0.2": "4. With Sumanā ",
    "an5.36:0.3": "Timely Gifts ",
    "an5.36:1.1": "“Mendicants, there are these five timely gifts. ",
    "an5.36:1.2": "What five? ",
    "an5.36:1.3": "A gift to a visitor. ",
    "an5.36:1.4": "A gift to someone setting out on a journey. ",
    "an5.36:1.5": "A gift to someone who is sick. ",
    "an5.36:1.6": "A gift at a time of famine. ",
    "an5.36:1.7": "Presenting the freshly harvested grains and fruits first to those who are ethical. ",
    "an5.36:1.8": "These are the five timely gifts. ",
    "an5.36:2.1": "The wise give at the right time, ",
    "an5.36:2.2": "being bountiful and rid of stinginess. ",
    "an5.36:2.3": "A religious donation at the right time ",
    "an5.36:2.4": "to the noble ones, upright and unaffected, ",
    "an5.36:3.1": "given with a clear and confident mind, ",
    "an5.36:3.2": "is indeed abundant. ",
    "an5.36:3.3": "Those who rejoice at that, ",
    "an5.36:3.4": "or do other services, ",
    "an5.36:3.5": "don’t miss out on the offering; ",
    "an5.36:3.6": "they too have a share in the merit. ",
    "an5.36:4.1": "So you should give without holding back, ",
    "an5.36:4.2": "where a gift is very fruitful. ",
    "an5.36:4.3": "The good deeds of sentient beings ",
    "an5.36:4.4": "support them in the next world.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an5.36:3.5": "Na tena → na tesaṁ (bj, pts1ed, mr) "
  },
